Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper focuses on natural language understanding and proposes a new inference task based on crime drama. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper uses multi-modal data including visual input from crime scenes and suspects to aid in perpetrator identification. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a new dataset and develops a model using LSTM-based learning to solve the inference task. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses machine learning techniques to develop the model and improve accuracy. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper uses multi-modal data including visual and acoustic input to aid in perpetrator identification.
